<gpx xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/1" xmlns:gpxx="http://www.garmin.com/xmlschemas/GpxExtensions/v3" creator="CALTOPO" version="1.1"><metadata><name><![CDATA[Diablo Canyon]]></name></metadata><trk><name>Diablo Canyon</name><desc>Popularity: 3/5
Difficulty: 1/5
Dates: 10/1 - 6/1

Diablo Canyon is an iconic canyon formed by the erosion of a 2.5 million year old lava lake. The canyon exposes massive basalt columns, hundreds of feet tall which are popular with rock climbers.

This out-and-back route is a very easy 6 miles following Arroyo Cañada Ancha, the waterway which carved out Diablo Canyon. You can run all the way to the Rio Grande, or turn around early. If you ask me I'd suggest going all the way to the Rio Grande for a satisfying turnaround point. Sorry about the trash at the river, some people like to drive their vehicles down there to camp and burn stuff...not cool.</desc><trkseg><trkpt lat="35.80456532010675" lon="-106.13624499660017"><ele>1782.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80458" lon="-106.13626"><ele>1782.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80452" lon="-106.13665000000003"><ele>1779.0596264003625</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80467" lon="-106.13713000000001"><ele>1779.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80479" lon="-106.13734999999997"><ele>1778.0425854621656</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80528" lon="-106.13855000000001"><ele>1775.666136080348</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80525" lon="-106.13873999999998"><ele>1774.8578467222949</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80505" lon="-106.13887"><ele>1773.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80542" lon="-106.14083"><ele>1769.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80567" lon="-106.14138000000003"><ele>1767.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80632" lon="-106.14204000000001"><ele>1769.75143029592</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80652" lon="-106.14267999999998"><ele>1766.130683619629</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.8066" lon="-106.14300000000003"><ele>1760.016856318815</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80664532440551" lon="-106.14302685890698"><ele>1760.6466320375603</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80671300154139" lon="-106.14306696381021"><ele>1761.0306236300123</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80687" lon="-106.14315999999997"><ele>1780.607359266768</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80689" lon="-106.14337999999998"><ele>1766.2311312137765</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80675" lon="-106.14386999999999"><ele>1758.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80655" lon="-106.14429999999999"><ele>1755.0</ele></trkpt><trkpt lat="35.80672" lon="-106.14453000000003"><ele>1758.99342538